GroupName: Common Transfer Rules Copied from the Library
RulesName: Copied from Library:  When main verb's Time is Discourse and subordinate clause's verb is Present, set subordinate tense to Discourse
Comment: Infected Eye 1:7  Alex knew that Melissa's eyes were sick.  The verb in the object complement has a Tense of Present.  None of these tense correction rules apply to the beginning of a direct quote.  These rules do apply to Direct Quotes because the quote may be a story.  So whenever the main verb's Time is Discourse, these rules apply.  Luke 9:19  The apostles answered, "Some people say ...  This rule doesn't apply if the subordinate verb is future tense.  Ruth 1:18  Naomi understood that Ruth would not return to her parents' house.  Gnomic Aspect may still cause the subordinate verb to be Present Tense.  Daniel 5:21  Nebuchadnezzar realized that God rules men's kingdoms.-*-  Luke 5:20  Jesus knew that these men believed that he was able to cause this man to become well.  Luke 7:19  John told his disciples to ask Jesus, "Are you the Messiah?"-*-  Esther 1:13  The king talked to men who knew the law well.-*-  Esther 4:2  The king's guards did not allow people that were wearing clothes that were made of sackcloth to enter the palace.-*-  Esther 3:13  The letter said that the people may take away all the things that the Jews owned.-*-  Daniel 1:20  These men were always able to answer all the questions that the king asked them.-*-  Daniel 6:4  No man was able to prove that Daniel did bad things.-*-  Don't change the tense of a Direct Quote.  Ruth 2:5 Boaz asked the leader of the workers, "Who is that young woman?"-*-  Don't change the tense of a Direct Quote.  Ruth 2:5 Boaz asked the leader of the workers, "Who is that young woman?"-*-

RulesName: "Scribe" a man that teaches people about the laws that Moses wrote -> Scribe
Comment: Luke 5:17  Some Pharisees and some people that teach people about the law that Moses wrote ...  Note that this doesn't apply if the relative clause is descriptive as in Neh. 8:1 Ezra, who taught the people about the law, ...-*-  Luke 11:45 A man that knew Moses' Law well ...-*-

RulesName: 'live again' -> 'rise from the dead'
Comment: Philippians 3:11  I will rise from the dead.-*-  Mark 6:14  -*-

RulesName: "demon" evil spirit
"widow" a woman whose husband died -> widow
"lots" stones that have marks
"breastplate" piece of metal that covers a soldier's chest
"wool" sheep's hair
'to hang' X kills Y by hanging X in a tree -> X hangs Y
"virgin" girl that did not sex a man -> virgin
Comment: OFF This structure is for Plural nouns; we want 'virgins' rather than 'some virgins.'    Gen. 19:8 I have two daughters that are virgins.-*-  OFF This structure is for Singular nouns; we want 'a virgin.'  2 Samuel 13:2  Tamar was a virgin. -*-  For Plural First Mention or Generic nouns, we want 'virgins' rather than 'some virgins.'  Esther 2:3  The officials brought all the beautiful young virgins to the palace. Esther 2:4:5 -*-  For Plural Routine nouns'  Esther 2:3  The officials brought all the beautiful young virgins to the palace.-*-  For singular nouns, we want 'a virgin.'-*-

RulesName: "vulture" a bird that eats dead animals -> vulture
"deacon" -> special servant of the church
"to welcome" X greets Y kindly -> X welcomes Y
Comment: Luke 9:5  If the people do not welcome you, ...-*-

RulesName: "miracle" an event that only God is able to do
Comment: Luke 23:8 Herod wanted to see Jesus do a miracle.-*-  Mark 6:5  -*-  Mark 6:52-*-

RulesName: COMBINE "miracle" = action done using God's power OR action that only God can do

RulesName: "to tempt" X tells Y to do bad things -> X tempts Y
Comment: Luke 4:2  While Jesus was in the desert, the devil told Jesus to do bad things.-*-  Mark 1:12  Satan tempts Jesus.-*-

RulesName: "to starve" X dies [because X does not have food]
Comment: But I might die [because I do not have food] (Bible stories 48:5).-*-

RulesName: "to stone" X kills Y by throwing stones at Y -> X stones Y
Comment: Exodus 17:4  These people will kill me soon by throwing stones at me. -> These people will stone me soon.-*-

RulesName: "furnace" a big container that contains a very hot fire
"lamb" a young sheep -> lamb
"thorny" plants that have sharp points -> thorny plants
"to sink" X goes under the top of the water
Comment: Luke 5:7  The two boats began to sink.  "sink" is in Longman's Defining Vocabulary, so it's not marked as complex.-*-

RulesName: "Law" religious laws -> Law
"manger" box that contains food for animals -> manger
Comment: Luke 2:12  The baby will be lying down in a box that usually contains food for animals.-*-

RulesName: "hymn" a song that's about God
Comment: Mark 14:26  After the disciples sang a hymn, ...-*-

RulesName: "merchant" person that sell things -> merchant
Comment: Nahum 3:16  You invited people that sell things ...-*-

RulesName: "messenger" people that carry messages -> messenger
"to sprout" seed starts growing
"wineskin" bag that contains wine
"myrrh" an expensive substance that people used so that they wouldn't have a lot of pain
"to thresh" X separates the grain from the plants
"to faint" to stop being conscious
"to rebuke" X tell Y that the things that Y said/did are bad -> X rebuke Y
